{
  "texts": [
    "ASTs are commonly used in computer science and programming language theory to analyze and manipulate code.",
    "Each node in an AST corresponds to a syntactic element of the code, such as a statement, expression, or declaration.Hu et al. [181] proposed Deepcom, a technique to preserve the structural information of the code intact by parsing the source code into an AST.",
    "The authors designed a new traversal strategy, structurebased traversal (SBT), which solves the problem that the source code cannot be effectively restored from the AST sequence.",
    "Subsequently, they proposed Hybrid-DeepCom [182] based on DeepCom, which mainly improves DeepCom in three aspects.",
    "First, it uses a combination of code information and AST sequence information."
  ]
}